title: Grateful Dead Live at Blossom Music Center on 1985-06-25
description:
Set 1

Day Tripper-> West L.A. Fadeaway-> CC Rider, Dire Wolf, Beat It On Down The Line-> Row Jimmy, Me & My Uncle, Big River, Big Railroad Blues, Jack Straw-> Might As Well

Set 2

Gimme Some Lovin'-> China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Playin' In The Band-> China Doll-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Touch Of Gray

reviews.review_text:
Jerry in Red This is my favorite recording of the show
the others have a hiss that appears and goes away very quickly but it is piercing and comes back again
this recording also keeps the energy feeling

5 star show (yet to find a non 5 star show;))

Major Highlights off the top of my head:
day tripper opener
Row Jimmy (A+)
Me n my Uncle
Jack Straw
Gimme some Lovin'
Touch Encore: Song always brings hope
The Playin' is where the magic is at, something about it always brings me back...beautiful chaos and Jerry is just going off, he has something to say and is saying it. Brent and drummers also have a little melt at the end
very scary space and a very eerie china doll
while you are here check out the playin'
might as well?(~);}

If anyone has the second set on tape i'm willing to trade
I have the first set but not the second!
Sugar Mags Love the mid-1980s Sugar Mags, and this is a corker... nice long jam pre-SSDD, unstoppable crashing rhythm, they are a machine chewing up everything before them!
